From 5c4e047943f582bde295dd335a5f6f6a9a8f99b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: StanleyYP Wang <StanleyYP.Wang@mediatek.com>
Date: Wed, 14 Jan 2026 11:26:35 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 249/260] mtk: hostapd: fix dfs issue for using the same
 channel for both bkg and main radio

Do not check the control channel when verifying whether the target
channel for background radar is same as the channel of the main radio.
Without this patch, the background radar will be forced to select the
same channel as the main radio, resulting in the AP interface going down
when radar is detected.
For example, in country MA, where only one 160MHz is allowed (ch36~64) for 5G
radio, if the bandwidth is set to 160MHz and the control channel is
not 36, then the background radar will still be set to channel 36 bw 160
since the control is not the same.
In this case, when radar is detected, the FSM will assume that the main radio
can switch to the channel of the background radar.
However, since both the channel of the background radar and the main radio are the
same, the channel switch would fail, resulting in AP interface going down.

Signed-off-by: StanleyYP Wang <StanleyYP.Wang@mediatek.com>
---
 src/ap/dfs.c | 5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/dfs.c b/src/ap/dfs.c
index f8aa0df0d..c2780ee47 100644
--- a/src/ap/dfs.c
+++ b/src/ap/dfs.c
@@ -1018,9 +1018,8 @@ int hostapd_handle_dfs(struct hostapd_iface *iface)
 		channel = dfs_get_valid_channel(iface, &sec, &cf1, &cf2, channel_type);
 
 		if (!channel ||
-		    (channel->chan == iface->conf->channel &&
-		    cf1 == hostapd_get_oper_centr_freq_seg0_idx(iface->conf) &&
-		    cf2 == hostapd_get_oper_centr_freq_seg1_idx(iface->conf))) {
+		    (cf1 == hostapd_get_oper_centr_freq_seg0_idx(iface->conf) &&
+		     cf2 == hostapd_get_oper_centr_freq_seg1_idx(iface->conf))) {
 			wpa_printf(MSG_ERROR, "Background radar could not get valid channel\n");
 			iface->radar_background.channel = -1;
 			return 0;
-- 
